transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Hey, hello?

Speaker 2: Yes, how can I help you?

Speaker 1: Yes, I was calling to see about canceling a membership.

Speaker 2: I wasn't aware that when I purchased the product that it came with a monthly subscription.

Speaker 1: I didn't want the subscription.

Speaker 2: I just wanted the phone.

Speaker 1: It doesn't unless you choose to.

Speaker 2: You can use the order.

Speaker 1: I can change it for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, can you check it for me?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm looking at your account now.

Speaker 2: Troy Riley?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Yeah, we can change that for you so you don't have to get it monthly.

Speaker 1: Okay, yes.

Speaker 2: I'd like to change it to just this one-time order and if it works for me I'll see about ordering it again.

Speaker 1: Well, yeah, so basically what we would do is keep your prescription open for like the next five months and you don't have to call in for any more refills in that time.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, would you like my extension?

Speaker 2: I can actually help you out with that if you do call in for an order.

Speaker 1: Let me get a paper to write on.

Speaker 2: Okay, what's your number and what's the extension?

Speaker 1: 0035.

Speaker 2: 0035?

Speaker 1: Okay, and let me ask you this.

Speaker 2: It's not going to charge me or anything during the five months unless I refill it, correct?

Speaker 1: Correct, yes, and you can also cancel that whole thing at any moment in that time.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay.

Speaker 1: As long as I don't get charged and I have the option to call back and refill it, I'll do that then.

Speaker 2: So thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Correct, and that's why I gave you the extension, too, because you can call.

Speaker 2: I can place those orders and then make sure everything stays this way for you after that.

Speaker 1: Okay, and what's your name again, sir?

Speaker 2: Quinn, Q-U-I-N-N.

Speaker 1: Q-U-I-N-N.

Speaker 2: Okay, Quinn, thank you so much, man.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: You're welcome, sir.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You, too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
